verbose_text: Possible explanations for the fact that most miRNAs did not show an increase in mature levels are : (i) that the pre-miRNA levels were low at the beginning of the experiment, over-expression of Exportin-5 would not change mature levels because there would be no excess pre-miRNA to export from the nucleus; (ii) it was shown that Exportin-5 contributes to the stability of the pre-miRNA.
